text.tspan: Merge happens between siblings, one will be source and another target.
Either of source or target can be atmost half filled.
And one of them is neccesarily be less than half filled .
This change shall be propogated to parent, sibling and child nodes as well.
Target is the one with smaller items than compared to source.
So Target is alwasy left sibling of source.
All items from source are copied to target. So no need to change the key in
parentNode as the key there is already smallest.
if leftMostchild is non leaf than it will not keep the minimum
Aftre merge source's parentCell is deleted. the minimum value from
leftMostChild is pulled and pushed in new merged cell. newMergedNode is
created out from Node of target [after copying all source cell in target],
so it has same parent-child and left sibling relation.
